The paper describes the development and validation of a machine reading system for extracting data from scientific literature, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves the use of ML algorithms for data extraction and inference, which falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the creation of a probabilistic database that improves as more information is added, which is related to the sub-category of Databases (cs.DB). The validation of the system's performance involves comparing it to human performance, which is a common evaluation metric in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval from scientific literature, which is related to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
